An archived version of the DRDID's std_ipw_did_panel without the fastglm function

Source: R/std_ipw_did_panel_archive.R
std_ipw_did_panel_archive.Rd

An archived version of the DRDID's std_ipw_did_panel without the fastglm function

Usage

std_ipw_did_panel_archive(
  y1,
  y0,
  D,
  covariates,
  i.weights = NULL,
  boot = FALSE,
  boot.type = "weighted",
  nboot = NULL,
  inffunc = FALSE
)

Arguments

y1

The post-treatment vector

y0

The pre-treatment vector

D

The binary treatment vector

covariates

The matrix or vector of covariates to train weights

i.weights

Sample weights. Default is NULL.

boot

A logical as to whether to bootstrap. Default is FALSE.

boot.type

Type of bootstrap. Default is a weighted bootstrap.

nboot

Number of bootstraps

inffunc

A logical as to whether to report the influence function or not.

Value

Returns an object with calculated ATT, standard error, confidence intervals, and influence functions.

Examples

std_ipw_did_panel_archive(rep(1,20),rep(0,20),c(1,rep(0,19)),c(70,rep(50,9),rep(80,10)))
